    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-03-31T00:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-03-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="693"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d693">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.711/74: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="#p_JNT1" type="from"
                            >Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-03-31T13:00:00+08:00"
                            >March 31, 1932—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 31—6:24 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>394. Following from American Consul General, Mukden: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Japanese <hi rend="italic">gendarmerie</hi> have begun censoring mail
                            matter in the <pb facs="0757" n="653" xml:id="pg_653"/> Chinese post
                            office—so far only Chinese newspapers—addressed to local foreigners,
                            several papers for Americans having been detained. Request instructions
                            regarding filing protest with the Japanese Consulate General.</p>
                        <p>Information has been received from Antung that Chinese Deputy Postal
                            Commissioner, Antung, was arrested by the Japanese <hi rend="italic"
                                >gendarmerie</hi> and held 9 hours, his office and residence being
                            thoroughly searched, no other details.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Legation proposes to instruct <persName corresp="#p_MMS1">Myers</persName> to
                    protest informally to Japanese Consul General if detention continues.</p>
                <closer>For the Minister:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
